The paper deals with the problem of oblivious subspace embeddings, which is a topic in both data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the sparsity of the embeddings, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's results have implications for distributed and streaming environments, which are topics in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and systems and control (cs.SI).
